RADIO COMMUNICATIONS

Radio items allow you to broadcast and receive messages on specific
frequency channels.  Two players on the same channel and the same radio
type can hear each other anywhere in the game world.

COMMANDS
  radio on              turns your radio on (begins receiving)
  radio off             turns your radio off
  tune <frequency>      changes to a different channel (1-100)
  transmit <message>    broadcasts a message on your current channel
  radio <message>       shorthand for transmit

CHANNELS
  Channel 14 is the Praxis open frequency (civilians).
  Channel 1 is the CS military coordination frequency.
  Other channels may be used by guilds, factions, or arranged groups.

RADIO TYPES
  Personal radio        short range, civilian grade
  Military radio        extended range, scan capable, CS-issue

TIPS
  Anyone on the same channel with a compatible radio will hear your
  transmission.  This is in-character communication, not OOC chat.
  For out-of-character communication use the 'ooc' command instead.

